00:06:22,826 --> 00:06:27,207
We had to pack down our new office that we had just moved into, move back home, and...

74
00:06:27,627 --> 00:06:34,091
This was a really difficult period for us as I'm sure lots of people listening to this can relate to

75
00:06:34,091 --> 00:06:41,434
having to maintain the same sort of production output, but have your

76
00:06:41,434 --> 00:06:47,998
working life and personal life completely upended while you've got these, you know, international pressures going on.

77
00:06:49,381 --> 00:06:53,382
So May comes around and we have to delay again.

78
00:06:53,382 --> 00:06:55,463
Things are getting blown out.

79
00:06:55,463 --> 00:06:59,284
The world is reeling from what's going on.

80
00:06:59,284 --> 00:07:01,384
Timelines are impossible to predict.

81
00:07:01,384 --> 00:07:04,105
And the one good thing about this period

82
00:07:04,105 --> 00:07:07,966
was that community was largely really supportive

