00:13:44,231 --> 00:13:47,312
So I did a very scientific survey on Twitter.

173
00:13:47,312 --> 00:13:49,713
I asked a few questions to developers

174
00:13:49,713 --> 00:13:52,775
who had released at least one commercial title.

175
00:13:53,919 --> 00:13:59,662
And these are some topics that I've been thinking about since release, and even now, almost a year

176
00:13:59,662 --> 00:14:06,365
later, still releasing patches, still releasing content, still releasing seasonal content to

177
00:14:06,365 --> 00:14:15,569
eke out some exposure in sales. And although this isn't quite the traditional sense of

178
00:14:15,569 --> 00:14:20,291
Games as a Service as I mentioned, the endpoint of games is moving further and further and further

179
00:14:20,291 --> 00:14:20,351
out.

180
00:14:21,247 --> 00:14:26,234
We are a continual service if we want a fighting chance these days,

181
00:14:26,234 --> 00:14:30,059
and we are providing continual support, and in a lot of cases,

182
00:14:30,059 --> 00:14:31,721
updates and content if we want to be seen.

183
00:14:31,721 --> 00:14:35,045
And this has a cost, like not in terms of...

184
00:14:36,067 --> 00:14:42,491
this is more work that I have to do, but you never really get closure on things at the moment if you

185
00:14:42,491 --> 00:14:51,617
want to buff your long tail or if you are super interested in maximizing the worth of your game

186
00:14:51,617 --> 00:14:52,177
over time.

187
00:14:53,097 --> 00:14:57,179
So the first question, did you patch your title within 24 hours of releasing?

188
00:14:57,179 --> 00:15:01,301
This includes making a patch build, submitting it to a platform review queue,

189
00:15:01,301 --> 00:15:04,102
or making a patch build and pushing it to users live.

190
00:15:04,102 --> 00:15:06,923
75 people surveyed, 76% said yes.

191
00:15:06,923 --> 00:15:11,906
So this already shows that there is a very like on-call nature in terms of

192
00:15:11,906 --> 00:15:16,248
games, that there is a very immediate expectation that issues are supposed

193
00:15:16,248 --> 00:15:17,729
to be fixed very quickly.

194
00:15:17,729 --> 00:15:22,371
And that I feel is another pressure that we have to acknowledge here.

195
00:15:23,783 --> 00:15:27,705
How many patches did you push within seven days of release?

196
00:15:27,705 --> 00:15:31,747
54 people responded and 85% said one to three.

197
00:15:31,747 --> 00:15:33,728
And I acknowledge this question's very broad

198
00:15:33,728 --> 00:15:35,949
because we don't know the length and breadth

199
00:15:35,949 --> 00:15:36,569
of those patches.

