00:16:18,054 --> 00:16:23,958
eye on issues that crop up, issues in Steam reviews, and plan into production where feasible

210
00:16:23,958 --> 00:16:27,220
to mitigate these sorts of things happening after release.

211
00:16:27,460 --> 00:16:32,642
you want to fix them, you want to add content, and if you want to keep your community happy,

212
00:16:32,642 --> 00:16:38,743
you need to be almost on call, watching the social media channels, keeping an eye on emails,

213
00:16:38,743 --> 00:16:43,065
vetting content creators, doing interviews, responding to reviews that present issues,

214
00:16:43,065 --> 00:16:48,006
stay on steam. So production and launch are really only the tip of the iceberg in terms of

215
00:16:48,006 --> 00:16:49,046
production cycles.

216
00:16:49,927 --> 00:16:55,829
and it plunges us straight into this games as a continual service cycle that feels like a

