00:17:08,636 --> 00:17:14,779
with 75% saying yes. I feel like this is also concerning because it is showing that

220
00:17:15,457 --> 00:17:24,161
we have that on-call nature after release, we are so worried about how negative things like bugs or

221
00:17:24,161 --> 00:17:30,844
less than stellar experiences, which I'm sure no developer wants their consumers to have and is

222
00:17:30,844 --> 00:17:37,727
more than happy to fix, the pressure from having to fix these because of the impact of things,

223
00:17:37,727 --> 00:17:40,148
of like say negative Steam reviews.

224
00:17:40,948 --> 00:17:48,990
is becoming more and more of a pressure, and we're having to respond to it quicker and quicker.

225
00:17:48,990 --> 00:17:56,792
We're expected to be continually responsive in launch windows, turn things around at an almost

